Here is some sample code to read data from a file and output it to the console in Java:

```java
import java.io.File;
import java.io.FileNotFoundException;
import java.util.Scanner;

public class ReadFile {

  public static void main(String[] args) {

    try {
      File myObj = new File("filename.txt");
      Scanner myReader = new Scanner(myObj);
      while (myReader.hasNextLine()) {
        String data = myReader.nextLine();
        System.out.println(data);
      }
      myReader.close();
    } catch (FileNotFoundException e) {
      System.out.println("An error occurred.");
      e.printStackTrace();
    }

  }

}
```

The key steps are:

1. Create a File object with the file path 
2. Create a Scanner object to read the file
3. Use hasNextLine() and nextLine() to read each line
4. Print out the line using System.out.println()
5. Close the Scanner when done

Make sure to handle any potential FileNotFoundException.

This will open the file, read each line, print it to console, and close the file when finished. You can modify it to fit your specific needs.
